[DAY 42] OPTIMISTIC vs PESSIMISTIC LOCKING:

  PESSIMISTIC (SELECT ... FOR UPDATE):
    - Locks the row immediately on read.
    - No concurrent readers allowed.
    - High contention serializes threads.
    - Use when: conflict rate is HIGH (bank account debited 1000x/sec).

  OPTIMISTIC (@Version):
    - No lock on read. Multiple concurrent readers.
    - On write: WHERE version = <current> → 0 rows → exception.
    - Loser must retry (reload and re-attempt).
    - Use when: conflict rate is LOW (typical for 99% of apps).

  @Version SQL:
    UPDATE users SET balance=?, version=1 WHERE id=? AND version=0
    If rows_affected=0 → StaleObjectStateException (Hibernate)
    Spring wraps it as OptimisticLockingFailureException.

